instructions: Sign in to your Play Console . Select an app. On the left menu, click Release management > Device catalog . Select the All Devices tab. To download a list of devices that are specific to your app, select Supported devices or Excluded devices . Near the right side of the page, click Download device list .

Open the Google Home app on your phone. Tap the speaker you want to use. Tap the icon with three lines at the top-right of your screen. How to change Google Home EQ settings How to change Google Home EQ settings How to change Google Home EQ settings Source: Joe Maring / Android Central
